<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[156, 106, 920, 139]]<|/det|>
Initially the road is horizontal and he runs at a constant speed of \(3\mathrm{m}\mathrm{s}^{-1}\). The athlete produces a constant power of \(60\mathrm{W}\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[156, 152, 547, 170]]<|/det|>
Find the resistive force which acts on the athlete.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[890, 152, 920, 170]]<|/det|>

The speed of the athlete at the start of this section of road is \(3\mathrm{m}\mathrm{s}^{- 1}\) and he now produces a constant driving force of \(24\mathrm{N}\). The total resistive force which acts on the athlete along this section of road has constant magnitude \(13\mathrm{N}\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[156, 373, 920, 391]]<|/det|>
Use an energy method to find the speed of the athlete at the end of the \(150\mathrm{m}\) section of road. [6]

The particle is kept in equilibrium by a horizontal force of magnitude \(P\mathrm{N}\) acting in a vertical plane containing a line of greatest slope (see diagram). The coefficient of friction between the particle and plane is 0.4.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 313, 390, 332]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 72, 920, 129]]<|/det|>
A particle \(P\) starts at rest and moves in a straight line from a point \(O\). At time \(t\) s after leaving \(O\), the velocity of \(P\), \(\nu \mathrm{m} \mathrm{s}^{- 1}\), is given by \(\nu = bt + ct^{\frac{3}{2}}\), where \(b\) and \(c\) are constants. \(P\) has velocity \(8\mathrm{m}\mathrm{s}^{- 1}\) when \(t = 4\) and has velocity \(13.5\mathrm{m}\mathrm{s}^{- 1}\) when \(t = 9\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[116, 141, 146, 159]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[158, 141, 400, 159]]<|/det|>

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 293, 920, 361]]<|/det|>
Two particles \(P\) and \(Q\), of masses \(2\mathrm{kg}\) and \(0.25\mathrm{kg}\) respectively, are connected by a light inextensible string that passes over a fixed smooth pulley. Particle \(P\) is on an inclined plane at an angle of \(30^{\circ}\) to the horizontal. Particle \(Q\) hangs below the pulley. Three points \(A\), \(B\) and \(C\) lie on a line of greatest slope of the plane with \(AB = 0.8 \text{m}\) and \(BC = 1.2 \text{m}\) (see diagram).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 373, 920, 421]]<|/det|>
Particle \(P\) is released from rest at \(A\) with the string taut and slides down the plane. During the motion of \(P\) from \(A\) to \(C\), \(Q\) does not reach the pulley. The part of the plane from \(A\) to \(B\) is rough, with coefficient of friction 0.3 between the plane and \(P\). The part of the plane from \(B\) to \(C\) is smooth.

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[116, 435, 146, 453]]<|/det|>
<label>(a)</label>
